    <section class="cb-who" aria-label="Which agency handles common Campbell issues">
      <span class="cb-who-label">Who actually fixes that?</span>
      <h2 class="cb-who-heading">Half the city isn't the city.</h2>
      <p class="cb-who-sub">Living in Campbell means dealing with <strong>seven different agencies</strong> wearing similar uniforms. Use this when your first instinct ("call the city") is wrong — and you'd spend 20 minutes on hold to learn it.</p>

      <div class="cb-who-grid">
        <article class="cb-who-card">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">🕳️</span>Pothole on a neighborhood street</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency">City of Campbell · Public Works</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why">Most residential streets, sidewalks, and street trees are city-maintained. But <strong>Hamilton Ave, Bascom, San Tomas Expy</strong> get handed off — see the next card.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">Report online: <a href="https://www.campbellca.gov/1049/Report-A-Concern" target="_blank" rel="noopener">campbellca.gov/Report-A-Concern</a></p>
        </article>

        <article class="cb-who-card">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">🛣️</span>Pothole on SR-17, San Tomas Expy, or Hamilton</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency cb-who-agency--gold">CalTrans + County Roads</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why">SR-17 is state (<strong>CalTrans District 4</strong>). Expressways like San Tomas + Lawrence are <strong>Santa Clara County</strong>. The city can't fix what it doesn't own.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">SR-17: <a href="https://csr.dot.ca.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">csr.dot.ca.gov</a> · County: <a href="https://www.sccgov.org/sites/rda" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sccgov.org/rda</a></p>
        </article>

        <article class="cb-who-card">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">🚨</span>Theft, noise, traffic stop, welfare check</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency cb-who-agency--red">Campbell PD (in-house)</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why">One of the few Bay Area cities still running its <strong>own</strong> police department. Non-emergency dispatch is staffed 24/7 — you don't have to wait for 911 for parking gripes.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">Non-emergency: <strong>408-866-2101</strong> · 911 for in-progress</p>
        </article>

        <article class="cb-who-card">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">🔥</span>House fire, medical call, gas leak</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency cb-who-agency--red">Santa Clara County Fire</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why">Surprise — Campbell <strong>contracts</strong> fire and EMS from County Fire (same engines that cover Los Gatos, Saratoga, Cupertino). Station 14 is the in-city house.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">911 only · Info: <a href="https://sccfd.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sccfd.org</a></p>
        </article>

        <article class="cb-who-card">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">💧</span>Water service or a leaking main</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency">San Jose Water Co.</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why">The water utility is a <strong>private company</strong> — confusingly named for a different city. The bill, the meter, the pipe under the street: all SJW, not Campbell.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">24/7 emergencies: <strong>408-279-7900</strong></p>
        </article>

        <article class="cb-who-card">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">🗑️</span>Trash, recycling, yard waste, bulky pickup</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency cb-who-agency--green">West Valley Collection (Recology)</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why">A four-city joint authority handles your bins. The city sets the rates; Recology runs the trucks. Each household gets <strong>two free bulky-item pickups</strong> a year.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">Schedule pickup: <a href="https://www.recology.com/recology-south-bay" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recology.com/south-bay</a></p>
        </article>

        <article class="cb-who-card">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">🚆</span>Vasona light rail, bus, or paratransit</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency">VTA (Santa Clara County)</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why">VTA runs the <strong>Vasona line</strong> (two Campbell stops: Downtown and Winchester) and every bus in town. The city has zero say in schedule or fare — that's VTA's board.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">Trip planner: <a href="https://www.vta.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">vta.org</a></p>
        </article>

        <article class="cb-who-card">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">🎒</span>School registration — K-8 vs. high school</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency cb-who-agency--gold">Two separate districts</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why"><strong>Campbell Union</strong> (K-8) and <strong>Campbell Union High</strong> (9-12) are <strong>different agencies with different boundaries</strong>. Your address can be in one and not the other — verify before you tour.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">K-8: <a href="https://www.campbellusd.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">campbellusd.org</a> · HS: <a href="https://www.cuhsd.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cuhsd.org</a></p>
        </article>

        <article class="cb-who-card" style="background: rgba(192, 57, 43, 0.04); border-left-color: var(--cb-red); border-style: dashed;">
          <p class="cb-who-issue"><span class="cb-who-icon">⚠️</span>"My address says Campbell but…"</p>
          <span class="cb-who-agency cb-who-agency--red">95008 ≠ City of Campbell</span>
          <p class="cb-who-why">The <strong>95008 ZIP</strong> covers chunks of unincorporated county and bits of San Jose. If you're in a county pocket, the sheriff polices you, the county permits your remodel, and city forms won't go anywhere.</p>
          <p class="cb-who-action">Check status: <a href="https://www.sccplanning.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sccplanning.org</a> parcel lookup</p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <p class="cb-who-foot">If the agency you're calling shrugs and says "not us," you're probably one rung off on this chart — try the next-most-likely owner before giving up.</p>
